I WANT TO GIVE PERMISSION TO SPECIFIC USER TO TAKE ACCESS OF ANOTHER LAPTOP DIRECTORY HOW CAN I DO THAT ?
ANS: setfacl -m "u:user:permissions" /path/to/file


https://testbook.com/interview/linux-lvm-interview-questions

RUn Leveles: 
Runlevel 0 : shutdown the system 
Runlevel 1: Single user 
Runlevel 2: multi-user mode without networking
Runlevel 3: multi-user mode wih networking 
Runlevel 4 : User-difinable
RunLevel 5: multi-user mode with networking 
RunLevel 6: Reboot 
